r>If the shissar spawns in the Amy temple, amys are up and there's less than 14 hours until the next raid then you have to honor the reservation on the armor mobs or figure a way of pulling the shissar without touching the Amys and other armor mobs?<br><br>Similar arguments for the golems...<br><br>(Just trying to make things clear in my own mind).<br><br>Ddrak <p><img src="http://www.chase.net.au/images/ddrak.gif" alt="Ddrak NFyre"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhuamak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khuamak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 11:33:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=45.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear FCFS rules...what are they please</span><hr size=1> Well..since the addition of epic weapons, shouldnt this be looked at and changed?  Show me someone headed to Fear that doens't care about their epic.  You need to be lvl 46 to even get up there.  Show me someone lvl 46 that isn't concerned about his/her epic and you will find someone that already HAS their epic.  <br><br>The plane of fear is NOT just about armor mobs anymore.  Its about armor and epic items.  I have a list a mile long for people that need their sk blade or shaman tear or wizard oil..etc.  I personally attempt to get those that have been on that list longest their opportunity to get the item.  Most of the time their opportunity is non existant due to spawn times.  The other times the opportunity was taken from them by another guild that feels its members have more rights to the spawn.<br><br>&quot;The raiding system was never about epic mobs&quot;...fine..isnt it time it was changed?  Or do some guilds have the rights to get what they need first and the others are too inferior to be considered?  We're not peasants.  All guilds should honor reservations for fear as they do for Naggy/Vox.  If the raid prior fails to take down mobs (except Cazic) then the attempt should be given to the next raid.<br><br>I plan Fear raids according to what should be spawned.  I spend the week prior to the raid finding out what should be up..or could be up.  I add groups accordingly.  When we finally get up there am I supposed to say to those people I added that they can leave because &quot;guild b&quot; was more important than they were and took the mobs we needed you to be here for?  I know you can only raid 2 or 3 times a month because of your schedule..but the other people are more important than you are...you dont deserve the chance to get your epic until they and all their alts have theirs.<br><br>Is there even room for discussion in this?  Or am I beating a dead horse?<br><br>Khuamak Zek<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r It's a zero exp rez.</span><br>  Posts: 1642<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 11:52:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=45.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Friends/LilKegger.gif WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fear FCFS rules...what are they please</span><hr size=1> It's pretty simple, as long as the reservations only cover armour drops then we're content to let them stay.<br><br>The moment you try to reserve epic mobs t